# InsightNerd — OpenHands Instructions

This is a Next.js 16 blog/portfolio site deployed to GitHub Pages at insightnerd.in.

## Project structure
- `src/app/` — Next.js App Router pages (layout.tsx, page.tsx, etc.)
- `src/components/` — React components (Navigation, Footer, animations, UI)
- `src/content/posts/` — MDX blog posts (do NOT modify unless explicitly asked)
- `src/content/.manifest.json` — Content manifest (do NOT modify)
- `scripts/fetch_and_publish.py` — Daily content agent (do NOT modify)
- `public/` — Static assets

## Tech stack
- Next.js 16.2.10 + React 19 + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Framer Motion / Motion for animations
- MDX for content

## Engineering conventions
- Run `npm run lint` before finishing changes
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` to type-check
- Prefer existing utility components from `src/lib/utils.ts` and `src/components/ui/`
- Use Tailwind utility classes, not custom CSS
- Keep React Server Components as the default; add 'use client' only when needed
- Match the existing code style — minimal comments, clean structure

## Content rules
- NEVER modify files in `src/content/` or `scripts/`
- NEVER modify `.github/workflows/` unless the task explicitly asks
